		<a href="/~giulioprisco">giulioprisco</a> writes <i>US economists are <a href="https://bitcoinmagazine.com/19330/fedcoin-rising/">considering a government-sponsored digital currency</a>. On February 3, David Andolfatto, Vice President of the Federal Reserve Bank of St. Louis, wrote a blog post based on a <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WrTsVg7V31Y">presentation he gave at the International Workshop on P2P Financial Systems 2015</a> [YouTube video]. The title of the blog post is "<a href="http://andolfatto.blogspot.co.uk/2015/02/fedcoin-on-desirability-of-government.html">Fedcoin: On the Desirability of a Government Cryptocurrency</a>."</i>
	</div>

	

	

	
	</div>
